      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Bank on Every Corner?</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Building Binge for Bank Branches'' (Square Feet, April 22):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Building Binge for Bank Branches'' (Square Feet, April 22):</p>
        <p>Especially in the new era of Internet banking, one may think that it doesn't make much fiscal sense to have so many bank branches in one neighborhood. But some people still want to connect a face with the money they are investing. To me, building more branches is a good investment all around.</p>
        <p>Steven M. Clayton  Ocean, N.J., April 22</p>
      </block>
